James Cabello Pixel Art (TI)

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

A model trained off of James Cabello "artwork" (https://twitter.com/JamesCabello_) Does not compare to the original, but does have a unique look.

Trained on NovelAI (clone) for 10k steps off of 61 images. Compatible with other TI's and LoRAs. I recommend a weight of 1.1 or less. Works on all models, ironically worst results with the model it was trained on.

Clip skip can be 1 or 2, but who is running without it? Actually running without clip skip seems to always remove the text and occasionally get better results. Text might also get canceled out depending on other TIs and LoRAs used.

bad_prompt Negative Embedding

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

bad_prompt Version 1 and 2 (reupload from Huggingface)

Foreword

Since alot of people asked for it. Here is a reupload to civitai for my negative Embedding.

Disclaimer: A new negative embedding is still under develop and I will upload it on civit soon!

~Text from Huggingface~

Link: https://huggingface.co/datasets/Nerfgun3/bad_prompt

Idea

The idea behind this embedding was to somehow train the negative prompt as an embedding, thus unifying the basis of the negative prompt into one word or embedding.

Side note: Embedding has proven to be very helpful for the generation of hands! :)

Usage

To use this embedding you have to download the file aswell as drop it into the "\stable-diffusion-webui\embeddings" folder.

To activate the embedding, you will have to write the name of the file in the negative prompt!

Please put the embedding in the negative prompt to get the right results!

For special negative tags such as "malformed sword", you still need to add them yourself. The negative embedding is trained on a basic skeleton for the negative prompt, which should provide a high-resolution image as a result.

Version 1:

Issue: Changing the style to much.

~not downloadable on civit~

Version 2:

With this version I tried to reduce the amount of vectors used, aswell as the issue with the changing artstyle. The newer version is still a work in progress, but its already way better than the first version. Its in files section!

To use it in the negative prompt: "bad_prompt_version2"

I hope you enjoy the embedding. If you have any questions, you can ask me anything via Discord: "Nerfgun3#7508"

Sara Underwood

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

Sara Jean Underwood is an American model, actress and TV host. She was the Playmate of the Month of July 2006, and Playmate of the Year in 2007.

1500-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images with my usual settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (s4runderwood:0.99), a woman, RAW, close portrait photo, long brown coat, long haircut, pale skin, slim body, (high detailed skin:1.2), 8k uhd, dslr, soft lighting, high quality, film grain, Fujifilm XT3 sharp focus, f 5.6"

BottomlessGirl

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

I noticed that on some models there is a problem that would depict a girl in any clothes, but without panties, with a naked bottom. You need to enter a lot of tokens, and play with their weights. This textual inversion was created to simplify this task.
__

Я заметил что на некоторых моделях существует проблема в том, что бы изобразить девушку в какой либо одежде, но без трусов, с голым низом. Необходимо ввести очень много токенов, и играть с их весами. Данная текстовая инверсия создана что бы упростить эту задачу.

Kim Basinger (70s/80s)

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

A commission of @Springbok707.

Kim Basinger is an American actress and model, winner of an Academy Award and known for roles in many notable films, including Batman and L.A. Confidential. My goal with this embedding was to somehow capture her looks of the late 70s and 80s.

This is a 1200-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images (partly provided by @Springbok707) with my usual settings. However, this time I've tried a couple of new things: I left the initialization text completely blank (usually I leave a "*" symbol instead) and reduced the token count to just 2 (it's usually 5 for me). I think the results have been very good, so I may keep these settings in the future.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (youngk1m:0.99), a woman, RAW, close portrait photo, long brown coat, long haircut, pale skin, slim body, (high detailed skin:1.2), 8k uhd, dslr, soft lighting, high quality, film grain, Fujifilm XT3 sharp focus, f 5.6"

Kaylin Slevin

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

v1: This inversion of Kaylin Slevin (Instagram Bimbo) was trained on 18 images (including flipped ones) at 2600 steps on v1.5-pruned and pairs very well with Fake Lips: https://civitai.com/models/18264 for a bit of 'authenticity'. I got best results with s1dlxbrew: https://civitai.com/models/4717/ as a checkpoint.

This is my first upload, feel free to be cruel. v1 had the vector tokens set to 8 so you may need to (full body:1.6) or more to get past south of her navel in your pics. Best results at 768x768. Best placed early in prompt for accuracy. (note in the second 768x1024 pic her iris' are InPainted blue)

v2: Trained at 2550 steps at a variable rate on v1.5-pruned, works more consistently across more checkpoints but I still got best results with s1dlxbrew. Same dataset as V1 but upscaled and refined more carefully with less vector tokens making her more flexible when using text2img.

Style Swamp Magic

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

This is my sixth publicly released Textual Inversion, called Style-Swampmagic. This model was trained on a single image using DreamArtist. This TI gives things as the name implies, a swampy/earthy feel. Things come out extremely mossy with foliage anything that you can imagine when you think of swamps!

The strength of the TI output depends on the prompt used and can range from subtle to overwhelming. It's important to adjust the weights or where you put the TI in the order of the prompt.

All display images have been upscaled, so the seeds/parameters for 1:1 image replication will not be correct. I am working on adding the original prompts/seeds to the description of each image. However, even with this information, it may be challenging to replicate an image exactly 1:1. You can refer to this comment for further explanation: https://civitai.com/models/14065/faetastic?commentId=69125&modal=commentThread

If you're interested in upscaling images to achieve high-quality results, I've written a guide that you may find helpful: https://ko-fi.com/post/The-Double-Headed-Issue-E1E0JO2UV
